OL,3,CMum's 'guilt' at persuading son to go
OL,4,Cto school on day he was stabbed
OL,6,FMrs Willgoose said her son struggled
OL,7,Fin school. She told ITV News: "I feel
OL,8,Fguilty, because we goaded him 'you
OL,9,Fneed to go to school'... I feel like
OL,10,Fwe led him into the lion's den. He
OL,11,Fdidn't want to go.
OL,13,F"I just feel terrible."
OL,15,FMrs Willgoose is calling for knife-
OL,16,Fdetecting airport-style scanners to be
OL,17,Finstalled in schools as standard.
OL,19,FBut she said the education system
OL,20,Fneeds to be re-evaluated to meet the
OL,21,Fneeds of different children.
