OL,3,CMum's 'guilt' at persuading son to go
OL,4,Cto school on day he was stabbed
OL,6,F"Just the week before we were saying
OL,7,Fthere's nowhere for kids to go, where
OL,8,Fthey can play their music and
OL,9,Fsocialise, not on their phones," Mrs
OL,10,FWillgoose said.
OL,12,FMr Willgoose said: "We don't want
OL,13,Fanyone else to suffer the same as we
OL,14,Fhave."
OL,16,FRonnie Tucker, who runs a local boxing
OL,17,Fclub, knows the family and is backing
OL,18,Ftheir calls for more provision for
OL,19,Fyoung people.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/6
